## App Description

StudyScape is a web application designed to help University of Washington students find optimal study locations on and around campus. This platform provides a detailed directory of study spots, allowing users to filter by key amenities such as Wi-Fi, food availability, noise levels, and accessibility features. Reviews, ratings, and photographs from students help provide a comprehensive perspective on each location. The goal is to make it easier for students to discover and choose study environments that best suit their preferences and needs.

## How to install software

1. Clone the repository: git clone [https://github.com/Study-Scape/StudyScape.git](https://github.com/Study-Scape/StudyScape.git)  
2. Install dependencies: npm install  
3. Set up environment variables: Locate provided .env.example file in study-scape directory  
4. Rename to .env.local  
5. Add the required API keys (message a StudyScape team member)  
6. Start the development server: npm run dev

## How to run software

The live version of StudyScape is hosted at: [https://study-scape.netlify.app/](https://study-scape.netlify.app/). The application supports all desktop browsers.

## How to use software

* Explore Study Locations on the Map:  
  * The homepage features an interactive map displaying markers for study spots on and around campus.   
* Browse Study Locations:  
  * Click the “Show All Locations” button to view a list of available study spots.  
  * Each listing includes details such as its address, amenities, rating, noise level, and accessibility features.   
* Search/Filter for Locations:  
  * Use the search bar in the Location List to find locations by name.   
    ![][image1]![][image2]  
    ![][image3]  
      
  * Use the provided filters to filter for locations that contain specific amenities (Wi-Fi, Food, Restrooms, Printers).  
    ![][image4]![][image5]

* About Page:  
  * Displays statistics such as the total number of study spots mapped, the average rating, and the number of students helped.  
  * Includes testimonials from users describing their experiences with StudyScape.  
    ![][image6]  
* Bookmarks Page:  
  * Users can save their favorite study spots for easy access.  
  * Bookmarked locations are displayed on this page for quick reference.   
    ![][image7]  
* Profile Page:   
  * Displays the user’s UW profile information.  
  * Shows their favorite study spots and study preferences.  
  * Lists the number of reviews they have left and their average rating.  
    ![][image8]  
* Work in Progress Features:  
  * View Location Details:  
    * Users will be able to click on a location to see more details, including photos, reviews, and ratings from UW students.   
  * Add Review or Rating to Spot  
    * Users will be able to add a rating or upload a review to a study spot they have visited.   
  * Route path to Location:  
    * Users will be able to get directions to a study spot directly from the map.

## Reporting a bug

If you encounter any issues, please report it in our GitHub issue tracker with the following details: 

* A clear description of the issue(s)  
* Steps to reproduce the bug  
* Expected behavior vs. actual behavior  
* Screenshots of issues (if applicable)  
* Device and browser information


All *known* bugs and limitations will be documented in our GitHub Issues. If you experience an issue that is not listed, please report it there.
